WEBVTT

00:10.144 --> 00:12.580
- * ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:12.613 --> 00:13.714
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:13.747 --> 00:21.689
*

00:35.569 --> 00:37.571
- * CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:37.605 --> 00:43.577
*

00:46.314 --> 00:49.817
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:49.850 --> 00:53.587
* CUE THE PULSE
TO BEGIN *

00:53.621 --> 00:56.056
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:59.127 --> 01:00.694
[moaning]

01:00.728 --> 01:04.332
[clattering]

01:10.538 --> 01:13.474
[both grunting]

01:20.414 --> 01:23.484
- COME HERE, COME HERE,
COME HERE, COME HERE.

01:26.487 --> 01:31.259
- [grunting]

01:31.292 --> 01:33.327
OH, THAT FEEL...
- FEEL GOOD, BABY?

01:33.361 --> 01:34.728
- YEAH, YEAH. THAT'S IT.

01:34.762 --> 01:35.863
YEAH, RIGHT THERE.
DON'T STOP.

01:35.896 --> 01:38.199
[doorbell rings]

01:38.232 --> 01:40.201
RIGHT THERE,
DON'T STOP. DON'T STOP.

01:40.234 --> 01:41.535
- [growls]

01:41.569 --> 01:43.337
- KEEP GOING, I'M COMING.
- OH, YEAH.

01:43.371 --> 01:44.338
[doorbell rings]

01:44.372 --> 01:47.208
- AH, FUCKIN' DOORBELL.

01:47.241 --> 01:49.243
- I'M COMING, I'M COM--
I'M COMING!

01:49.277 --> 01:51.512
- [panting]
COME ON.

01:51.545 --> 01:53.347
- OH, YEAH.

01:53.381 --> 01:55.416
[doorbell rings]

01:55.449 --> 01:56.550
- OH!

01:58.319 --> 02:00.188
- HELLO, SIR.
I'M CHARLOTTE

02:00.221 --> 02:01.889
AND THIS IS AMANDA,
AND WE'RE HERE TO TALK TO YOU

02:01.922 --> 02:03.624
ABOUT PROPOSITION 14.

02:03.657 --> 02:04.925
ARE YOU AWARE OF IT?

02:04.958 --> 02:06.760
- YES, I'M AWARE OF IT.
- GOOD.

02:06.794 --> 02:09.230
THEN WE NEEDN'T TELL YOU
HOW IMPORTANT IT IS THESE DAYS

02:09.263 --> 02:11.265
TO PROTECT THE HOLY BONDS
OF MATRIMONY,

02:11.299 --> 02:12.633
AND THE AMERICAN FAMILY.

02:12.666 --> 02:14.535
- ISN'T THAT THE
GOD'S-HONEST TRUTH?

02:14.568 --> 02:15.536
- ARE YOU MARRIED?

02:15.569 --> 02:16.537
- I MOST CERTAINLY AM.

02:16.570 --> 02:17.938
- WELL, IN THAT CASE,

02:17.971 --> 02:19.907
WE'D LOVE TO SPEAK
WITH YOU AND YOUR WIFE.

02:19.940 --> 02:22.910
- HONEY, THERE ARE SOME
VERY SWEET LADIES HERE

02:22.943 --> 02:26.314
URGING US TO SUPPORT
PROPOSITION 14.

02:26.347 --> 02:27.315
- DO YOU HAVE CHILDREN?

02:27.348 --> 02:28.916
- A SON AND A DAUGHTER.

02:28.949 --> 02:30.651
- OH, THAT'S WONDERFUL.

02:30.684 --> 02:32.186
- GOOD AFTERNOON,
LADIES.

02:32.220 --> 02:33.787
- THIS IS MY LAWFULLY
WEDDED HUSBAND.

02:33.821 --> 02:37.525
- AND THIS IS MY
LAWFULLY WEDDED HUSBAND.

02:37.558 --> 02:39.527
AND WE ARE GOING TO DO
EVERYTHING IN OUR POWER

02:39.560 --> 02:42.330
TO DEFEAT
PROPOSITION 14.

02:42.363 --> 02:43.431
- I SEE.
- OKAY.

02:43.464 --> 02:45.266
- WELL, GOOD
AFTERNOON THEN.

02:45.299 --> 02:46.567
- HEY, THANKS FOR
STOPPING BY.

02:46.600 --> 02:47.568
- WE'LL BE SURE TO VOTE.

02:47.601 --> 02:50.571
- BYE-BYE.

02:57.578 --> 02:58.946
- I CAUGHT THAT.

02:58.979 --> 03:00.414
- CAUGHT WHAT?

03:00.448 --> 03:01.849
- THAT SUBTLE EXCHANGE
OF SMILES

03:01.882 --> 03:03.717
THAT CAN INDICATE
ONLY ONE THING:

03:03.751 --> 03:06.687
"IS YOUR ASS
AS SORE AS MINE?"

03:06.720 --> 03:08.356
- FUCKING CHRIST,
THEODORE,

03:08.389 --> 03:09.957
IS THERE ANYONE IN THIS BURG
YOU HAVEN'T BONED

03:09.990 --> 03:11.759
SINCE YOUR
EXTREME MAKE-OVER?

03:11.792 --> 03:13.427
- WELL, LET'S JUST SAY THAT

03:13.461 --> 03:15.229
IF THEY DON'T GET
A FRESH SUPPLY IN SOON,

03:15.263 --> 03:17.765
I'LL BE FORCED TO
MOVE TO PHILADELPHIA.

03:19.500 --> 03:20.901
YOU KNOW, I ALWAYS
USED TO WONDER

03:20.934 --> 03:23.471
WHAT IT'D BE LIKE TO
HAVE ANY GUY I WANTED.

03:23.504 --> 03:24.705
NOW I KNOW.

03:24.738 --> 03:26.474
- AND?

03:26.507 --> 03:30.478
- AND IT'S, UH, GREAT.

03:30.511 --> 03:33.581
HEY, LOOK WHO
IT IS. MICHAEL.

03:33.614 --> 03:34.848
- HEY, TEDDY.

03:34.882 --> 03:36.016
HEY, EM.

03:36.049 --> 03:39.253
- HI, SWEETIE.

03:39.287 --> 03:40.488
- WELL, IF YOU BOYS
WILL EXCUSE ME,

03:40.521 --> 03:43.223
I HAVE TO GET BACK TO WORK.

03:45.826 --> 03:49.229
- YEAH, I GOT TO GET
BACK TO THE STORE.

03:51.565 --> 03:52.866
- BUSY DAY?

03:52.900 --> 03:54.402
- YEAH. THIS COMIC BOOK
COLLECTION

03:54.435 --> 03:56.036
I BOUGHT OFF EBAY
JUST ARRIVED.

03:56.069 --> 03:58.606
IT'S GOING TO TAKE ME WEEKS
TO INSPECT AND GRADE THEM.

03:58.639 --> 04:00.808
- WELL, BETTER HAVE
SOMETHING TO EAT.

04:00.841 --> 04:01.775
WHAT'LL IT BE?

04:01.809 --> 04:03.544
- I THINK I'LL HAVE...

04:03.577 --> 04:04.678
- ARE YOU AND BRIAN
NEVER GOING

04:04.712 --> 04:06.280
TO TALK TO EACH OTHER AGAIN?

04:06.314 --> 04:07.881
- MA...
- MICHAEL,

04:07.915 --> 04:11.018
YOU'VE BEEN FRIENDS, BROTHERS,
SINCE YOU WERE KIDS.

04:11.051 --> 04:13.754
YOU LOVE EACH OTHER.

04:13.787 --> 04:16.657
YOU GOING TO LET A LIFETIME,
A FUCKING HISTORY,

04:16.690 --> 04:19.293
GO DOWN THE DRAIN 'CAUSE
OF SOME CHILDISH DISAGREEMENT?

04:19.327 --> 04:22.029
AND BELIEVE ME, I KNOW
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

04:22.062 --> 04:23.431
- IT'S NOT CHILDISH.

04:23.464 --> 04:26.367
AND IT'S NOT JUST
A DISAGREEMENT.

04:26.400 --> 04:27.801
HE DISRESPECTS EVERY CHOICE
I'VE MADE.

04:27.835 --> 04:30.638
HE MOCKS ME FOR WANTING
A FAMILY AND A HOME.

04:30.671 --> 04:32.373
HE CALLS ME A DEFECTOR.

04:32.406 --> 04:34.575
HE EVEN BLAMES ME FOR HIS
AND JUSTIN'S BREAK-UP.

04:34.608 --> 04:37.511
HE SAYS I INFECTED HIM.

04:37.545 --> 04:38.779
WELL, HE CAN THINK
WHATEVER HE WANTS,

04:38.812 --> 04:40.581
AND CALL ME
WHATEVER HE PLEASES.

04:40.614 --> 04:43.684
IT REALLY DOESN'T MATTER
ANYMORE.

04:43.717 --> 04:47.054
I'LL HAVE THE TUNA FISH
ON WHOLE WHEAT WITH A LEMON BAR.

04:47.087 --> 04:49.557
HOLD THE REMARKS.

04:51.725 --> 04:53.093
- WE'RE GOING
DOOR-TO-DOOR TODAY

04:53.126 --> 04:54.395
TO TRY AND GET PEOPLE
TO LISTEN.

04:54.428 --> 04:56.397
A LOT OF THEM
MAY NOT WANT TO,

04:56.430 --> 04:57.665
SO DON'T BE DISCOURAGED

04:57.698 --> 04:59.066
IF YOU GET DOORS SLAMMED
IN YOUR FACE.

04:59.099 --> 05:00.768
JUST BE COURTEOUS,

05:00.801 --> 05:01.969
MAKE YOUR POINT
SUCCINCTLY,

05:02.002 --> 05:04.938
AND WHATEVER YOU DO,
DO NOT ENGAGE.

05:04.972 --> 05:06.440
- THAT MEANS DON'T LOSE
YOUR FUCKING TEMPER

05:06.474 --> 05:07.841
AND SHOOT OFF
YOUR BIG MOUTH.

05:07.875 --> 05:09.843
- [chuckles]
EXACTLY. GOOD LUCK.

05:11.845 --> 05:13.347
- READY?
- YEAH.

05:13.381 --> 05:14.948
I HOPE THEY DON'T
COME OUT SWINGING,

05:14.982 --> 05:16.950
NOT WITH THE FORTUNE
I JUST SPENT ON MY FACE.

05:16.984 --> 05:18.886
- AH, AND WHAT A LOVELY FACE
IT IS TOO.

05:18.919 --> 05:20.821
YOU MUST GET
LOTS OF COMPLIMENTS.

05:20.854 --> 05:22.356
- I'M GETTING
MORE THAN THAT.

05:22.390 --> 05:24.825
HEH-HEH-HEH.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.894
BUT TO TELL
YOU THE TRUTH,

05:26.927 --> 05:28.496
SOMETHING'S MISSING.

05:28.529 --> 05:29.963
- LOVE, COMMITMENT?

05:29.997 --> 05:31.499
- YEAH, SOMETHING
LIKE THAT.

05:31.532 --> 05:32.966
- WHAT YOU NEED'S A HUSBAND.
- [scoffs]

05:33.000 --> 05:35.969
FIRST I NEED A BOYFRIEND.

05:36.003 --> 05:38.038
BUT WHAT WON'T BE EASY.

05:38.071 --> 05:39.973
MY STANDARDS ARE
RIDICULOUSLY HIGH.

05:40.007 --> 05:42.710
I WANT SOMEONE WHO'S
FINANCIALLY SECURE,

05:42.743 --> 05:44.612
WITH A FACE
LIKE BRAD PITT,

05:44.645 --> 05:45.913
A BODY LIKE BRAD PITT,

05:45.946 --> 05:48.716
AND HUNG LIKE...
WELL, JUST HUNG.

05:48.749 --> 05:50.651
- THAT'S NOT SO RIDICULOUS.
THAT'S ABSURD.

05:50.684 --> 05:52.586
LISTEN, IF YOU REALLY
WANT TO GET HITCHED,

05:52.620 --> 05:53.987
WHAT YOU NEED'S
A JEWISH GUY.

05:54.021 --> 05:55.155
THEY MAKE THE BEST
MARRIAGE MATERIAL.

05:55.188 --> 05:56.790
- THEY DO?
- YEAH, PROVIDED YOU CAN

05:56.824 --> 05:58.926
GET PAST THE INCESTUOUS
RELATIONSHIP THEY HAVE

05:58.959 --> 06:02.663
WITH THEIR MOTHERS THAT LASTS
BEYOND THE GRAVE.

06:02.696 --> 06:04.398
- GOOD AFTERNOON, SIR.

06:04.432 --> 06:05.866
WE'RE HERE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT PROPOSITION 14.

06:05.899 --> 06:08.168
WE'LL ONLY TAKE A MINUTE
OF YOUR TIME.

06:08.201 --> 06:11.539
- OR LESS.

06:11.572 --> 06:13.741
WELL, IT MAY NOT BE EASY,

06:13.774 --> 06:16.176
BUT AT LEAST IT GETS YOU
OUT OF THE HOUSE.

06:16.209 --> 06:17.878
- THAT'S WHAT
MICHAEL SAID:

06:17.911 --> 06:20.748
KEEPING BUSY WOULD TAKE
MY MIND OFF HUNTER.

06:20.781 --> 06:22.082
SO FAR IT HASN'T HELPED.

06:22.115 --> 06:24.418
- GIVE IT TIME.

06:24.452 --> 06:26.186
- HOW MUCH TIME?
A LIFETIME?

06:26.219 --> 06:27.521
BECAUSE THAT'S HOW LONG
IT'S GOING TO TAKE

06:27.555 --> 06:30.524
FOR ME TO FORGET ABOUT HIM.

06:33.126 --> 06:35.929
- OH, UH, WHAT CAN I DO
FOR YOU FOLKS?

06:35.963 --> 06:38.165
- WE'D LIKE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT PROPOSITION 14.

06:38.198 --> 06:40.033
- IT'S VERY IMPORTANT
THAT YOU VOTE NO.

06:40.067 --> 06:41.769
- WHY'S THAT, SON?

06:41.802 --> 06:43.904
- IF IT PASSES,
GAY MEN AND WOMEN

06:43.937 --> 06:45.939
WILL LOSE THE SAME RIGHTS
THAT OTHER AMERICANS HAVE.

06:45.973 --> 06:47.808
- AND WHO'S TO SAY
WHAT'S NEXT?

06:47.841 --> 06:50.043
THE ELDERLY COULD LOSE
THEIR SOCIAL SECURITY,

06:50.077 --> 06:52.580
WOMEN COULD LOSE THE RIGHT
TO HAVE AN ABORTION.

06:52.613 --> 06:54.515
- I SEE YOUR POINT.

06:54.548 --> 06:56.116
YOU'VE GOT MY VOTE.

06:56.149 --> 06:58.085
- DAD?

06:58.118 --> 07:00.053
WHO'S AT THE DOOR?
- HELLO.

07:00.087 --> 07:02.590
UH, WE WERE JUST
TALKING TO YOUR FATHER

07:02.623 --> 07:05.058
ABOUT VOTING NO
FOR PROPOSITION 14.

07:05.092 --> 07:07.928
- MY FATHER HASN'T VOTED
IN TEN YEARS.

07:07.961 --> 07:09.863
HE HAS ALZHEIMER'S.

07:09.897 --> 07:12.099
COME ON, DAD.

07:14.702 --> 07:16.904
- TRUST ME, JIM.

07:18.972 --> 07:20.541
LOOK, WHY DON'T WE
HAVE LUNCH TOMORROW?

07:20.574 --> 07:21.842
I'LL PLY YOU WITH MARTINIS.

07:21.875 --> 07:26.246
AND I GUARANTEE YOU WILL
SEE THINGS MY WAY.

07:26.279 --> 07:27.881
OH.

07:29.983 --> 07:33.487
FELDON'S LOSING HIS HARD-ON
FOR THE NEW HOME STATION AD.

07:33.521 --> 07:37.257
- WELL, YOU HAVE TO ADMIT,
IT'S A BIT SUGGESTIVE.

07:37.290 --> 07:40.994
- YOU ALSO HAVE TO ADMIT
IT'S GENIUS.

07:41.028 --> 07:42.630
- HEY LISTEN, HOW ABOUT
COMING WITH ME

07:42.663 --> 07:44.832
TO BETH EMMANUEL'S MIXER?

07:44.865 --> 07:47.868
- WHO'S SHE?
- IT'S A TEMPLE.

07:47.901 --> 07:50.103
THEY'RE HAVING THEIR MONTHLY
GAY GET-TOGETHER AT WOODY'S,

07:50.137 --> 07:52.573
AND I WANT TO
MEET A MENSCH,

07:52.606 --> 07:53.707
SETTLE DOWN.

07:53.741 --> 07:56.744
- CHRIST.
AM I THE ONLY FAG

07:56.777 --> 07:58.278
WHO DOESN'T WANT TO PUT
A TROUSSEAU TOGETHER

07:58.311 --> 08:00.681
AND WALK DOWN THE AISLE?

08:00.714 --> 08:03.250
- LISTEN, I'M NOT
GETTING ANY YOUNGER.

08:03.283 --> 08:06.720
I'LL BE 35 THIS SUMMER.
- 9.

08:06.754 --> 08:08.756
- WHAT?
- 39.

08:08.789 --> 08:11.892
- I--
- I'M YOUR EMPLOYER.

08:11.925 --> 08:13.994
THERE'S A PAPER TRAIL.

08:14.027 --> 08:16.296
WHY DON'T YOU ASK JUSTIN?

08:16.329 --> 08:18.165
RUMOR HAS IT HE'S HOT
FOR A HUBBY.

08:18.198 --> 08:20.000
- JUST THOUGHT I'D ASK.

08:20.033 --> 08:21.168
- WELL, THERE ARE
MANY UNCERTAINTIES

08:21.201 --> 08:22.870
IN THIS LIFE, THEODORE,

08:22.903 --> 08:25.639
MANY MYSTERIES
BEYOND OUR COMPREHENSION.

08:25.673 --> 08:27.274
BUT ONE THING
I KNOW FOR A FACT:

08:27.307 --> 08:30.578
I WILL NEVER BE
MRS. SEYMOUR GOLDFARB.

08:35.849 --> 08:38.018
- I WISH WE'D BEEN ABLE
TO CONVINCE MORE PEOPLE.

08:38.051 --> 08:40.654
- WELL, THE IMPORTANT THING IS,
WE KEEP ON TRYING, HUH?

08:40.688 --> 08:43.791
- YEAH.
- OH, UH--

08:45.693 --> 08:47.027
- AM I LATE?

08:47.060 --> 08:48.295
- UH, NO.

08:48.328 --> 08:50.664
WE JUST GOT HERE OURSELVES.

08:50.698 --> 08:53.767
- WHO'S HE?
- WE'LL TALK LATER.

08:53.801 --> 08:56.637
- WH--

08:56.670 --> 08:58.806
- HI.
- HI.

09:05.879 --> 09:08.849
- KEEP UP THE GOOD WORK,
HONEY.

09:29.837 --> 09:32.740
- HAVE YOU SEEN A LETTER
SIGNED BY JUDGE SALTZMAN?

09:40.280 --> 09:41.882
- WONDER HOW IT GOT
INTO MY PILE?

09:41.915 --> 09:44.151
- OH, BEATS ME.

09:46.253 --> 09:47.821
- YOU DIDN'T HAPPEN
TO SEE AN INVOICE

09:47.855 --> 09:49.890
FROM THE RESNICK GALLERY
IN NEW YORK, DID YOU?

09:51.324 --> 09:53.961
- OH, IT'S RIGHT HERE.

09:53.994 --> 09:56.664
MUST'VE GOTTEN MIXED UP
WITH MY STUFF BY MISTAKE.

09:58.398 --> 10:00.367
WHAT'S THIS?

10:00.400 --> 10:02.369
- OH, THAT'S A PIECE JUSTIN
HAS IN THE ART SHOW.

10:02.402 --> 10:06.239
WAIT TILL YOU SEE IT.

10:06.273 --> 10:08.008
YOU ARE COMING TO THE OPENING,
AREN'T YOU?

10:08.041 --> 10:11.011
- ACTUALLY, I'M SUPPOSED
TO GO OUT WITH, UH--

10:11.044 --> 10:14.147
- CORINNE.

10:14.181 --> 10:16.249
MEL, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO HIDE IT.

10:16.283 --> 10:17.651
THAT'S OUR ARRANGEMENT:

10:17.685 --> 10:19.286
YOU HAVE YOUR LIFE,
I HAVE MINE.

10:19.319 --> 10:21.421
- I KNOW, BUT I DON'T WANT
TO MAKE YOU FEEL UNCOMFORTABLE.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.724
IT'S YOUR SHOW.
- THAT'S RIGHT, IT'S MY SHOW.

10:23.757 --> 10:26.326
AND I'M INVITING YOU.

10:26.359 --> 10:28.395
AND CORINNE.

10:28.428 --> 10:29.730
- YOU SURE?

10:29.763 --> 10:31.264
- I'M FINE WITH IT.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.834
REALLY.

10:38.171 --> 10:39.807
[sighs]

10:39.840 --> 10:43.376
NOW WHAT HAVE I DONE
WITH "UNTITLED ONE AND TWO"?

10:45.913 --> 10:48.782
- IT'S RIGHT HERE,
UNDER NEWCOMBE VERSUS BUDGE.

10:51.785 --> 10:54.287
[indistinct chatter]

10:54.321 --> 10:56.323
[dog barking]

10:59.860 --> 11:02.162
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

11:02.195 --> 11:04.231
- OH, A GIRAFFE.
ISN'T THAT CUTE?

11:04.264 --> 11:05.298
- IT'S A SWAN.

11:05.332 --> 11:09.837
- OH, I CAN SEE THAT...
KIND OF.

11:09.870 --> 11:11.038
- IT'S FOR MY NEXT SEGMENT.

11:11.071 --> 11:13.040
THEY WANT SOMETHING CUTE.

11:13.073 --> 11:14.174
- THERE ARE A COUPLE
OF REPORTERS

11:14.207 --> 11:15.909
CAMPED OUT, OUT FRONT.

11:15.943 --> 11:17.210
- SHIT!

11:17.244 --> 11:18.712
- AND LOOK AT THIS.

11:18.746 --> 11:20.447
THEY TOOK
AN OLD PHOTOGRAPH OF ME

11:20.480 --> 11:22.783
AND MADE IT LOOK
LIKE I'M IN BABYLON.

11:22.816 --> 11:24.317
I'VE NEVER EVEN
BEEN TO BABYLON.

11:24.351 --> 11:26.219
- YOU KNOW, LAST WEEK
THEY PUT POOR LIZA'S HEAD

11:26.253 --> 11:28.321
ON THE BODY
OF A 400-POUND WOMAN.

11:28.355 --> 11:30.824
THEN SAID SHE WAS TOO FAT
TO GET OUT OF BED.

11:30.858 --> 11:33.460
- YOU CAN'T LET THAT TRASH
GET TO YOU.

11:33.493 --> 11:36.797
BESIDES, IT'LL ALL STOP
ONCE YOU COME OUT.

11:36.830 --> 11:39.399
- YOU'RE GOING TO COME OUT?

11:39.432 --> 11:42.002
WHEN? HUH?

11:42.035 --> 11:43.203
WHERE, HONEY?

11:43.236 --> 11:45.272
- I HAVEN'T DECIDED YET.

11:45.305 --> 11:47.841
- WELL, I SAY LARRY KING.

11:47.875 --> 11:50.744
I MEAN, IF IT WAS ME, I'D
DEFINITELY COME OUT TO LARRY.

11:50.778 --> 11:53.847
I MEAN, YOU KNOW, OF COURSE
HOWEVER YOU DECIDE TO DO IT,

11:53.881 --> 11:54.848
IT HAS TO BE YOUR WAY.

11:54.882 --> 11:56.216
- YEAH, DEB'S RIGHT.

11:56.249 --> 11:57.751
YOU'VE GOT TO DO IT
ON YOUR OWN TERMS.

11:57.785 --> 12:00.220
- OOH.

12:00.253 --> 12:02.255
YOU GOT SOME SAUCE
ON YOUR CHIN, BABY.

12:02.289 --> 12:03.991
- THAT WAS MY SWAN.

12:04.024 --> 12:05.225
- IT WAS A GIRAFFE, HONEY.

12:05.258 --> 12:07.761
[chuckles]
TRY AGAIN.

12:11.298 --> 12:12.900
YOU KNOW, I GOT ONE HELL
OF A NERVE.

12:12.933 --> 12:15.502
I'M SITTING HERE LIKE
SOME FUCKING EUNUCH

12:15.535 --> 12:17.504
MAKING ANIMALS
OUT OF NAPKINS,

12:17.537 --> 12:20.240
"TO DELIGHT THE GUESTS
AT YOUR NEXT DINNER PARTY."

12:20.273 --> 12:23.343
AND I'M TELLING YOU
HOW TO BE OUT AND PROUD.

12:29.282 --> 12:31.985
- IT'S A FUNNY STORY,
HOW WE MET.

12:32.019 --> 12:33.921
- I'M ALWAYS UP
FOR A LAUGH.

12:33.954 --> 12:36.423
- WELL, I-I WAS DROPPING MOLLY
OFF AT SCHOOL

12:36.456 --> 12:39.893
WHEN, WOULDN'T YOU KNOW,
I GET A FLAT.

12:39.927 --> 12:42.863
JUST THEN THIS MOTORCYCLE
COMES ROARING UP,

12:42.896 --> 12:45.065
AND THIS GUY DRESSED
ALL IN BLACK

12:45.098 --> 12:47.901
ASKS ME IF I WANT HELP.

12:47.935 --> 12:49.402
WELL, I HAD TAKEN
THAT NIGHT CLASS

12:49.436 --> 12:51.138
IN CAR MAINTENANCE
AFTER YOUR FATHER LEFT.

12:51.171 --> 12:54.441
BUT I-I WAS ON MY WAY
TO AN OPEN HOUSE.

12:54.474 --> 12:57.444
I DIDN'T WANT TO SHOW UP
LOOKING LIKE A GREASE MONKEY...

12:57.477 --> 13:00.881
[laughs]
SO I SAID YES.

13:00.914 --> 13:03.283
AND IT TURNED
OUT TO BE TUCK.

13:03.316 --> 13:05.318
- [snorts]
"TUCK"?

13:05.352 --> 13:07.955
- IT'S SHORT FOR TUCKER.

13:07.988 --> 13:11.058
HE TEACHES EIGHTH GRADE SCIENCE
AT MOLLY'S SCHOOL.

13:11.091 --> 13:14.094
- WOW. MY SIDES
ARE SPLITTING.

13:16.396 --> 13:19.466
- SO WE GOT TO CHATTING,

13:19.499 --> 13:21.168
HE ASKED ME
IF I WANTED TO GO OUT

13:21.201 --> 13:24.171
SOME NIGHT FOR A COFFEE.
- COFFEE?

13:24.204 --> 13:27.908
AREN'T HIS PARENTS AFRAID
IT MIGHT STUNT HIS GROWTH?

13:27.941 --> 13:29.910
- DO YOU WANT
TO HEAR THIS OR NOT?

13:29.943 --> 13:31.912
- [clears throat]

13:31.945 --> 13:34.915
- WELL, I FIGURED,
"WHAT THE HELL?"

13:34.948 --> 13:38.986
BEATS SITTING AT HOME READING
"HOW TO SURVIVE A DIVORCE,"

13:39.019 --> 13:41.054
SO I SAID YES.

13:41.088 --> 13:45.092
AND THE REST IS HISTORY.

13:45.125 --> 13:48.261
- FOR HIM MODERN,
FOR YOU ANCIENT.

13:48.295 --> 13:49.863
- I TAKE IT YOU
DON'T APPROVE.

13:49.897 --> 13:51.464
- [sighs]
I SUPPOSE A WOMAN OF YOUR AGE

13:51.498 --> 13:54.067
IS ALLOWED TO HAVE
A LITTLE FLING,

13:54.101 --> 13:56.603
PROVIDED IT'S DISCREET.

13:56.636 --> 14:00.073
- WELL, ACTUALLY, IT'S--

14:00.107 --> 14:01.875
IT'S MORE THAN
A LITTLE FLING.

14:01.909 --> 14:04.511
WE'VE BEEN SEEING EACH OTHER
FOR SIX MONTHS.

14:04.544 --> 14:06.479
- FOR SIX MONTHS?

14:06.513 --> 14:09.950
AND YOU NEVER
SAID ANYTHING?

14:09.983 --> 14:13.520
- WHAT WAS THE POINT,
UNTIL I WAS SURE IT WAS SERIOUS?

14:13.553 --> 14:15.488
- SERIOUS?
YOU ARE NOT SERIOUS.

14:15.522 --> 14:18.291
HE'S 1/3 YOUR AGE.
- HALF.

14:18.325 --> 14:20.393
- FINE, HALF.
HE'S HALF YOUR AGE.

14:20.427 --> 14:22.963
HE'S STILL YOUNG
ENOUGH TO BE YOUR S--

14:22.996 --> 14:25.098
I DON'T EVEN
WANT TO SAY IT.

14:25.132 --> 14:28.568
- AND I DON'T WANT
TO HEAR IT.

14:28.601 --> 14:30.370
ESPECIALLY FROM YOU.

14:30.403 --> 14:32.872
- IT'S THE TRUTH.

14:37.277 --> 14:39.512
[jazz music]

14:39.546 --> 14:43.316
[knock at door]

14:43.350 --> 14:46.086
[clears throat]

14:52.159 --> 14:55.695
[coughs]

14:55.728 --> 14:58.531
- YOU ALONE?

14:58.565 --> 15:01.001
- ONE OF THOSE RARE,
UNEXPECTED MOMENTS.

15:01.034 --> 15:04.171
- AH.

15:04.204 --> 15:06.673
- SO MUCH FOR THE MOMENT.

15:06.706 --> 15:10.677
- THAT THELONIOUS?

15:10.710 --> 15:13.947
- THAT, UH, TUNA-MACARONI
CASSEROLE?

15:13.981 --> 15:16.149
- YOU GOT IT.

15:16.183 --> 15:18.418
- DON'T WANT IT.

15:18.451 --> 15:20.420
TUNA CASSEROLE MEANS THAT
WE'RE GOING TO GET STONED

15:20.453 --> 15:23.623
AND HAVE A VERY
MEANINGFUL CONVERSATION.

15:23.656 --> 15:25.358
UNFORTUNATELY,

15:25.392 --> 15:27.427
I JUST FINISHED
MY LAST JOINT.

15:27.460 --> 15:30.630
- WELL, FORTUNATELY...

15:30.663 --> 15:33.600
I BROUGHT ONE WITH ME.

15:49.249 --> 15:50.617
- DOES DETECTIVE HORVATH KNOW

15:50.650 --> 15:53.320
THAT HIS BLUSHING BRIDE
IS A POTHEAD?

15:53.353 --> 15:55.355
- [chuckles]

15:55.388 --> 15:57.357
NOTHING KILLS A GOOD
RELATIONSHIP FASTER

15:57.390 --> 16:00.193
THAN FULL DISCLOSURE.

16:00.227 --> 16:02.629
- GIVE ME SOME OF THAT.

16:09.169 --> 16:12.639
- I DON'T LIKE THE WAY
YOU'VE BEEN TREATING MICHAEL.

16:12.672 --> 16:15.642
- BUTT THE FUCK OUT.

16:18.778 --> 16:20.480
- YOU'VE BEEN ON HIS CASE
EVER SINCE

16:20.513 --> 16:22.382
HE AND BEN
BOUGHT THAT HOUSE TOGETHER.

16:22.415 --> 16:25.252
- HE DIDN'T JUST
BUY A HOUSE.

16:26.819 --> 16:30.623
HE BOUGHT THE SLICER
AND THE DICER,

16:30.657 --> 16:32.359
THE GINZU KNIVES,
THE ABS-ROLLER,

16:32.392 --> 16:34.427
THE JUICER.

16:34.461 --> 16:36.163
THE TOP HUNDRED HITS
OF THE '60s,

16:36.196 --> 16:39.532
NOT AVAILABLE
AT ANY STORE.

16:39.566 --> 16:44.104
IN SHORT, EVERY
LIE, EVERY CON...

16:44.137 --> 16:48.541
EVERY COLOR,
SHAPE AND SIZE OF BULLSHIT

16:48.575 --> 16:51.511
THE STRAIGHT WORLD
HAS TO OFFER.

16:51.544 --> 16:54.514
- HE FELL IN LOVE.

16:54.547 --> 16:57.217
HE GOT MARRIED.

16:59.452 --> 17:02.122
HE HAD A FAMILY.

17:02.155 --> 17:07.294
YOU KNOW, EVERYTHING HE'S EVER
WANTED TO DO AS A KID.

17:07.327 --> 17:09.262
A NORMAL HOME.

17:09.296 --> 17:11.331
- [scoffs]

17:14.301 --> 17:17.170
- WHY DO YOU HAVE
SUCH A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

17:19.439 --> 17:22.142
I'LL TELL YOU WHY.

17:22.175 --> 17:24.177
YOU DON'T.

17:28.448 --> 17:30.483
YOUR PROBLEM IS...

17:33.186 --> 17:35.455
HE LEFT YOU.

17:38.491 --> 17:41.494
HE LEFT YOU,
AND HE MOVED ON.

17:44.731 --> 17:48.835
ONLY HE DIDN'T.

17:48.868 --> 17:53.206
YOU AND HE JUST MADE
DIFFERENT CHOICES, THAT'S ALL.

17:53.240 --> 17:57.210
IT DOESN'T MEAN THAT YOU DON'T
STILL LOVE EACH OTHER.

17:59.746 --> 18:02.615
- HE WON'T TALK TO ME.

18:02.649 --> 18:05.618
- THEN YOU TALK TO HIM.

18:11.758 --> 18:13.860
- THE MONEY BEHIND IT
IS UNBELIEVABLE.

18:13.893 --> 18:15.728
NOT JUST WEALTHY
CONSERVATIVES,

18:15.762 --> 18:17.530
BUT BIG CORPORATIONS.

18:17.564 --> 18:19.632
- UH, BEN SAYS WE SHOULD
BOYCOTT THEM.

18:19.666 --> 18:22.602
- YEAH, BEFORE THEY TAKE
THAT RIGHT AWAY FROM US TOO.

18:22.635 --> 18:24.504
SORRY TO SOUND LIKE
SUCH AN ALARMIST,

18:24.537 --> 18:26.606
BUT THESE DAYS I FEEL LIKE
I'M LIVING IN NAZI GERMANY,

18:26.639 --> 18:28.475
LIKE WE'RE THE NEW JEWS.
- OH, COME ON, MEL.

18:28.508 --> 18:29.776
DON'T YOU THINK THAT'S
GOING A BIT FAR?

18:29.809 --> 18:31.778
- LISTEN, MY ZAIDEH,
MY GRANDFATHER,

18:31.811 --> 18:33.213
HE USED TO TELL ME
EVERYBODY THOUGHT

18:33.246 --> 18:34.681
HE WAS NUTS
FOR LEAVING GERMANY.

18:34.714 --> 18:36.349
"OH, YOU'RE MAKING
TOO MUCH OF IT.

18:36.383 --> 18:38.751
IT'LL PASS.
THAT'LL NEVER HAPPEN HERE."

18:38.785 --> 18:40.753
HE DIED AT THE AGE OF 87.

18:40.787 --> 18:43.490
THE REST OF HIS FAMILY
DIED IN THE CAMPS.

18:43.523 --> 18:44.691
- WELL, WHAT'RE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO,

18:44.724 --> 18:46.359
PACK UP AND MOVE TO PARIS?

18:46.393 --> 18:49.496
- WELL, LAST TIME I HEARD,
THEY HAD A GAY MAYOR.

18:49.529 --> 18:51.231
LISTEN, I'M GOING
TO GRAB THIS CAB.

18:51.264 --> 18:53.400
- OKAY. OOH.
[chuckles]

18:53.433 --> 18:55.902
- OH, BYE, SWEETHEART.
- AWW, MEL.

18:55.935 --> 18:58.538
- [laughs]
I MEANT HER. YOU TOO.

19:01.308 --> 19:03.410
CAN YOU TAKE ME TO, UH...

19:13.553 --> 19:19.226
[alarm ringing]

19:28.368 --> 19:34.307
[alarm ringing]

19:59.599 --> 20:01.734
- NOTHING WAS STOLEN?

20:01.768 --> 20:03.570
- NOT THAT I CAN TELL.

20:03.603 --> 20:07.340
- ALL I CAN SAY IS,
THANK GOD NO ONE WAS HURT.

20:07.374 --> 20:09.442
- I'LL NEED YOU
TO FILE A REPORT.

20:09.476 --> 20:11.444
- THEN WHAT?
- WE'LL INVESTIGATE.

20:11.478 --> 20:13.313
BUT WITH THIS
KIND OF VANDALISM,

20:13.346 --> 20:15.582
IT'S USUALLY PRETTY DIFFICULT
TO COME UP WITH ANYTHING.

20:15.615 --> 20:16.983
- THAT'S ALL YOU THINK IT WAS?
VANDALISM?

20:17.016 --> 20:18.851
- WELL, WHAT ELSE?
PROBABLY JUST SOME KID

20:18.885 --> 20:20.653
TRYING TO STEAL
A COMIC BOOK.

20:20.687 --> 20:22.522
- WHAT IF IT WASN'T?

20:22.555 --> 20:24.724
WHAT IF THEY WERE TRYING
TO DESTROY THAT?

20:24.757 --> 20:27.394
TWO GAY SUPERHEROES,
GETTING MARRIED.

20:27.427 --> 20:28.995
- LOOK, I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE SUGGESTING,

20:29.028 --> 20:31.731
BUT THERE'S NO EVIDENCE
OF ANY HATE CRIME.

20:31.764 --> 20:32.932
- A HATE CRIME?

20:32.965 --> 20:35.502
- I APPRECIATE
YOUR CONCERN, BUT...

20:35.535 --> 20:36.936
IN ALL HONESTY,

20:36.969 --> 20:38.871
I THINK YOU'RE GETTING
A BIT CARRIED AWAY.

20:38.905 --> 20:40.640
- THAT'S FUNNY.

20:40.673 --> 20:43.543
I JUST ACCUSED MEL
OF THE SAME THING.

20:46.513 --> 20:48.815
- REMEMBER, MEN,
A SMARTLY-FOLDED NAPKIN

20:48.848 --> 20:50.950
WILL ADD A TOUCH OF CLASS
TO YOUR TABLE SETTING

20:50.983 --> 20:54.287
AND BE CERTAIN TO
CHARM YOUR LADY FRIEND.

20:54.321 --> 20:55.488
AND WHO KNOWS?
AFTER DINNER,

20:55.522 --> 20:57.290
SHE MIGHT EVEN...

20:57.324 --> 21:00.760
LET YOU SHOW HER HOW
TO MAKE ONE OF THESE.

21:00.793 --> 21:02.629
I'M EMMETT HONEYCUTT,
YOUR QUEER GUY,

21:02.662 --> 21:06.399
HERE TO MAKE YOUR LIFE
MORE FABULOUS.

21:06.433 --> 21:08.401
- THANKS, QUEER GUY,
AND THAT'S THE NEWS.

21:08.435 --> 21:10.837
WE'LL SEE YOU
TOMORROW AT 6:00.

21:10.870 --> 21:14.541
- UNTIL THEN, HOPE ALL
YOUR NEWS IS GOOD NEWS.

21:14.574 --> 21:16.709
- AND WE'RE OUT.

21:18.978 --> 21:20.580
CUTE SEGMENT, EMMETT.

21:20.613 --> 21:23.049
AND BY THE WAY, I'VE GOT
SOME GOOD NEWS FOR YOU.

21:23.082 --> 21:25.518
MANAGEMENT IS THINKING ABOUT
DOING A QUEER GUY SPECIAL.

21:25.552 --> 21:26.819
NOW HERE'S THE CONCEPT:

21:26.853 --> 21:28.921
YOU PREPARE AND
SERVE A GOURMET DINNER

21:28.955 --> 21:31.458
TO A HOT STRAIGHT COUPLE.

21:31.491 --> 21:33.526
- OH, PERFECT.

21:33.560 --> 21:35.928
AND AFTER, THEY CAN FUCK
WHILE I DO THE DISHES.

21:35.962 --> 21:36.996
- [laughs]

21:37.029 --> 21:38.465
- HEY, DON.
- YEAH?

21:38.498 --> 21:39.666
- YOU WON'T BELIEVE WHO
I JUST SPOKE TO.

21:39.699 --> 21:41.601
- WHO?
- DREW BOYD.

21:41.634 --> 21:43.436
HE WANTS TO GIVE ME
AN EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW

21:43.470 --> 21:45.472
ABOUT THE ALLEGATIONS
THAT HE'S A FAG.

21:45.505 --> 21:47.440
- JESUS CHRIST. OUR RATINGS
ARE GONNA GO THROUGH THE ROOF.

21:47.474 --> 21:48.941
- WATCH OUT CHANNEL 7.

21:48.975 --> 21:52.111
- OH MAN, THEY'LL BE
YESTERDAY'S NEWS.

21:52.144 --> 21:55.114
[techno music]

21:55.147 --> 21:56.949
*

21:56.983 --> 22:02.522
[indistinct chatter]

22:12.131 --> 22:15.067
- CAN I GET A CRANBERRY JUICE
AND SPARKLING WATER?

22:22.074 --> 22:23.976
- OH.
- OH, SORRY.

22:24.010 --> 22:25.111
- IT'S OKAY.
- NO, NO, NO.

22:25.144 --> 22:26.646
I'LL HAVE YOUR
SWEATER CLEANED.

22:26.679 --> 22:29.516
- AH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THE SWEATER.

22:29.549 --> 22:30.883
I'LL HAVE ANOTHER
DRINK THOUGH.

22:30.917 --> 22:32.452
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
OF COURSE, OF COURSE.

22:32.485 --> 22:34.754
UH, WHAT WERE YOU...
- DIET PEPSI.

22:34.787 --> 22:36.589
- YOU DON'T DRINK?

22:36.623 --> 22:39.459
- UH, MAYBE A GLASS OF WINE
ON OCCASION, HOLIDAYS,

22:39.492 --> 22:42.629
BUT, UH,
THAT'S ABOUT IT.

22:42.662 --> 22:44.597
- UM, TED SCHMIDT.
SHALOM.

22:44.631 --> 22:46.399
- ADAM BERNSTEIN.

22:46.433 --> 22:49.368
SHALOM AND, UH,
NICE TO MEET YOU TOO.

22:50.803 --> 22:52.739
SO WHAT DO YOU DO
FOR A LIVING?

22:52.772 --> 22:54.774
- WELL, I WORK
AT THIS AD AGENCY.

22:54.807 --> 22:56.175
I DO A LOT OF THINGS THERE
BUT, UH,

22:56.208 --> 22:58.144
MOSTLY, I'M AN ACCOUNTANT.
- AN ACCOUNTANT?

22:58.177 --> 22:59.679
YOU KNOW, MY BROTHER'S
AN ACCOUNTANT.

22:59.712 --> 23:01.948
MAYBE YOU'VE HEARD OF HIM?

23:01.981 --> 23:03.550
MARK BERNSTEIN?

23:03.583 --> 23:04.884
- YEAH, I THINK
I KNOW SEVERAL.

23:04.917 --> 23:06.085
[both chuckle]

23:06.118 --> 23:08.755
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
- UROLOGIST.

23:08.788 --> 23:10.557
- A DOCTOR.

23:10.590 --> 23:14.193
WELL, MY MOTHER'D
BE THRILLED.

23:14.226 --> 23:16.529
SO, UH, WHAT
ELSE DO YOU DO,

23:16.563 --> 23:21.033
I MEAN, BESIDES EXAMINING
GUYS' PROSTATES?

23:21.067 --> 23:22.635
- I'M A TENNIS FREAK.

23:22.669 --> 23:24.704
I MEAN, I'VE GOT
A HELL OF A BACKHAND.

23:24.737 --> 23:26.706
- I'LL BET YOU DO.

23:26.739 --> 23:27.807
DO YOU LIKE OPERA?

23:27.840 --> 23:30.643
- NO, HATE IT.

23:30.677 --> 23:32.512
UH, BUT I LOVE BALLET--

23:32.545 --> 23:34.046
MEN IN TIGHTS.

23:34.080 --> 23:36.716
HOW CAN YOU GO WRONG, RIGHT?
- RIGHT.

23:36.749 --> 23:38.718
I'VE GOT SEASON'S TICKETS.

23:38.751 --> 23:40.953
WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE GO SOMETIME?

23:40.987 --> 23:42.922
- YOU MEAN,
A "PAS DE DEUX"?

23:42.955 --> 23:44.557
I'D LOVE TO.

23:44.591 --> 23:46.192
- BUT THEN...

23:46.225 --> 23:49.962
WHY WAIT UNTIL "GISELLE"
ROLLS INTO TOWN?

23:49.996 --> 23:51.964
- OH.

23:56.569 --> 23:59.706
- HEY, I JUST PUT ONE OF THOSE
ON THE FRONT LAWN.

23:59.739 --> 24:02.675
- YEAH, AND I JUST
TOOK IT OUT.

24:02.709 --> 24:04.677
- WHAT?

24:04.711 --> 24:06.212
- AREN'T WE DOING ENOUGH?

24:06.245 --> 24:07.614
CANVASSING AND VOLUNTEERING?

24:07.647 --> 24:09.949
DO WE REALLY NEED THIS TOO?

24:09.982 --> 24:13.019
- IT'S A SIGN OF SOLIDARITY,
SUPPORT.

24:13.052 --> 24:15.087
BESIDES, PRACTICALLY EVERYONE'S
HOUSE ON THE BLOCK HAS ONE,

24:15.121 --> 24:16.956
INCLUDING ELI AND MONTY'S.

24:16.989 --> 24:18.257
- GOOD FOR THEM.
THEY CAN ALSO

24:18.290 --> 24:20.627
WEAR PINK TRIANGLES
ON THEIR SLEEVES.

24:20.660 --> 24:23.095
- NO REASON TO GET YOURSELF
SO WORKED UP.

24:23.129 --> 24:25.732
- ACTUALLY, THERE IS.
I'VE ALREADY BEEN A TARGET.

24:25.765 --> 24:28.835
- CARL SAID THERE'S
NO EVIDENCE OF THAT.

24:28.868 --> 24:32.705
LOOK, I KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
AT THE SHOP WAS UPSETTING.

24:32.739 --> 24:35.842
BUT LET'S TRY AND
STAY LEVEL-HEADED.

24:35.875 --> 24:37.243
- WELL, FINE.

24:37.276 --> 24:38.845
LET'S HOW LEVEL-HEADED
YOU FEEL WHEN THEY

24:38.878 --> 24:41.013
ROUND US ALL UP AND
TAKE US OFF TO THE CAMPS.

24:41.047 --> 24:42.849
- [scoffs]
ALL RIGHT.

24:42.882 --> 24:44.183
IF YOU DON'T WANT IT
ON THE FRONT LAWN,

24:44.216 --> 24:46.619
WE WON'T PUT IT
ON THE FRONT LAWN.

24:52.792 --> 24:57.163
- LOOK, I KNOW YOU THINK
I'M BEING RIDICULOUS, BUT...

24:57.196 --> 24:58.998
I WOULD HATE FOR SOMETHING
TERRIBLE TO HAPPEN

24:59.031 --> 25:02.101
JUST BECAUSE WE DIDN'T
PAY ATTENTION TO THE WARNINGS.

25:04.036 --> 25:06.539
- WE'LL HAVE MORE SCORES
AT 11:00. BUT RIGHT NOW,

25:06.573 --> 25:09.175
WE'VE GOT A SPECIAL GUEST
IN THE STUDIO WITH US,

25:09.208 --> 25:10.677
STAR QUARTERBACK
FOR THE IRONMEN

25:10.710 --> 25:14.146
AND TWO-TIME MVP DREW BOYD.

25:14.180 --> 25:16.215
GREAT TO HAVE YOU HERE, DREW.
- THANKS, BUD.

25:16.248 --> 25:18.284
- WELL, DREW, YOU'D HAVE
TO BE LIVING ON THE MOON

25:18.317 --> 25:20.887
NOT TO KNOW WHAT'S BEEN
HAPPENING WITH YOU THESE DAYS.

25:20.920 --> 25:23.890
I'M TALKING ABOUT THESE,
UH, SEX ALLEGATIONS.

25:23.923 --> 25:25.792
"BOYD LIKES BOYS."

25:25.825 --> 25:27.827
- IT'S BEEN A VERY DIFFICULT
TIME FOR ME,

25:27.860 --> 25:29.696
BUD, AS YOU CAN IMAGINE.

25:29.729 --> 25:32.565
BUT I FEEL AS THOUGH THE SOONER
THAT I ADDRESS THIS ISSUE,

25:32.599 --> 25:34.767
THE SOONER I CAN GET ON
WITH MY LIFE.

25:34.801 --> 25:36.669
- LET ME JUST SAY THAT
WE'VE KNOWN EACH OTHER FOR...

25:36.703 --> 25:38.571
HOW LONG NOW?
15 YEARS?

25:38.605 --> 25:40.573
WE STARTED OUT
PLAYING BALL TOGETHER.

25:40.607 --> 25:41.808
AND I'VE ALWAYS
THOUGHT OF YOU,

25:41.841 --> 25:43.910
NOT ONLY AS AN
OUTSTANDING ATHLETE,

25:43.943 --> 25:46.212
BUT AS A MAN'S MAN.

25:46.245 --> 25:47.647
SO, WHY DON'T WE PUT

25:47.680 --> 25:49.682
ALL THESE RUMORS
TO REST RIGHT NOW?

25:49.716 --> 25:51.183
- FIRST OF ALL,
I'D LIKE TO SAY THAT

25:51.217 --> 25:53.786
MOST OF THOSE STORIES
ARE OUT-AND-OUT LIES,

25:53.820 --> 25:55.655
TOTAL EXAGGERATIONS.

25:55.688 --> 25:58.725
- I'M SURE THAT'S A RELIEF
FOR YOUR MILLIONS OF FANS.

25:58.758 --> 26:01.794
- BUT IF YOU'RE ASKING
ME IF I'M GAY...

26:01.828 --> 26:05.564
THE ANSWER IS YES.

26:13.039 --> 26:15.341
- I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

26:15.374 --> 26:17.209
YOU'RE SAYING
A GUY LIKE YOU?

26:17.243 --> 26:21.013
- YEAH, A GUY LIKE ME.

26:21.047 --> 26:24.283
- AW, I-I CAN'T EVEN PICTURE
YOU KISSING ANOTHER GUY.

26:24.316 --> 26:26.085
NOT LIKE HIM.

26:26.118 --> 26:27.954
- EXCUSE ME?

26:27.987 --> 26:29.856
- ACTUALLY, BUD,

26:29.889 --> 26:33.025
IT WAS YOUR QUEER GUY,
EMMETT HONEYCUTT,

26:33.059 --> 26:34.393
WHO HELPED ME
TO FIND THE COURAGE

26:34.426 --> 26:37.263
NOT JUST TO BE
A MAN'S MAN...

26:37.296 --> 26:40.099
BUT TO BE MY OWN MAN.

26:40.132 --> 26:43.135
AND I'D LIKE TO THANK HIM.

26:58.184 --> 27:00.186
- WE'LL BE BACK
IN A MINUTE.

27:00.219 --> 27:01.721
- AND WE'RE OUT.

27:01.754 --> 27:07.626
[indistinct chatter]

27:10.029 --> 27:11.397
- JUSTIN.
- YEAH?

27:11.430 --> 27:13.132
- I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET
SIMON CASWELL.

27:13.165 --> 27:14.901
HE'S THE CRITIC FROM
THE "ART FORUM MAGAZINE".

